{"word":"H3554 - כָּוָה - kâvâh - kaw-vaw' - Burn","slug":"H3554","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">כָּוָה</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>kâvâh"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>kaw-vaw'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Burn"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05DB;&#x05BC;&#x05D5;&#x05D4; - ka&#x0302;va&#x0302;h</b> - <i>kaw-vaw'</i><p/>A primitive root; properly to <i>prick</i> or <i>penetrate</i>; hence to <i>blister</i> (as smarting or eating into): - burn."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H3555\">H3555</a>, <a href=\"#/H3587\">H3587</a>, <a href=\"#/H4348\">H4348</a>"}]}